executableContent.instructions:
Once the player guesses correctly, we don't want them to continue playing.

1.  If the player guesses correctly, end the game by setting `attempts` to `0` in the `if` block.

Your code should look like the following:
```JavaScript
while (attempts > 0) {
  if (guess == randomNumber) {
    attempts = 0;
    ...
    break;
  } else if (guess < randomNumber) {
    ...
    break;
  } else {
    ...
    break;
  }
}
```

